doc_id=118 page=1 block_id=1-4 bbox=71.99,156.2,539.39,654.91 label=bb 7 43
line=7 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=72.0,644.0,538.48,654.91                     :South  Asian languages  are well known  for possessing a large number  of complex  verbal constructions
line=8 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,630.44,538.95,641.35        :containing either a verb, a noun or an adjective as main predicator and a ‘light verb’ as the part of the
line=9 fonts=F0-10.9,F4-8.0 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,616.88,539.39,628.81 :construction which carries the tense and agreement morphology.^{1} Light verbs in these languages have long
line=10 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.33 bbox=72.0,603.44,538.89,614.35       :intrigued grammar  writers (e.g., Kellogg 1893, Chatterji 1926, McGregor 1968) and  linguists (e.g., Vale
line=11 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.15 bbox=72.0,589.88,539.03,600.79       :1948, Hook  1974), as the contribution of the light verb to the complex construction does not appear to be a
line=12 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.10 bbox=72.0,576.32,538.9,587.23        :purely functional one. This is especially evident with V-V sequences (main verb followed by a light verb)
line=13 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,562.76,538.49,573.67       :where the contribution of the light verb has often been characterized via aspectual terms such as perfectivity
line=14 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,549.2,538.78,560.11        :(Hook  1991, Singh 1994)  or inception/completion (Butt 1995), but also via semantically less well defined
line=15 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,535.64,538.88,546.55       :terms like forcefulness, suddenness, volitionality, benefaction, etc. The range of meanings is broad and
line=16 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.19 bbox=72.0,522.08,538.84,532.99       :appears to be related to the basic lexical semantics of the base verb that is involved (i.e., ‘take’ vs. ‘give’ for
line=17 fonts=F0-10.9,F4-8.0 iscore=0.05 bbox=72.0,508.52,323.27,520.45:benefaction, ‘fall’ for suddenness, ‘hit’ for forcefulness).^{2}
line=18 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.07 bbox=88.92,494.96,538.93,505.87      :    While the morphological and  syntactic properties of these verbal complex constructions have been de-
line=19 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,481.4,538.75,492.31        :scribed in some detail for South Asian languages, the precise semantic characterization of the role of light
line=20 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.28 bbox=72.0,467.84,539.07,478.75       :verbs remains  the subject of investigation and debate. This paper proposes to take a fresh look from a
line=21 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,454.28,538.54,465.19       :perspective which  presupposes a tight mapping  between  syntactic structure and semantic combinatorial
line=22 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.13 bbox=72.0,440.84,538.87,451.75       :possibilities. We aim to show that the morphosyntax of predicational structures is closely correlated with
line=23 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,427.28,538.85,438.19       :aspectual and event-structure notions in semantic representation. Our primary language of investigation is
line=24 fonts=F0-10.9,F4-8.0 iscore=0.19 bbox=72.0,413.72,538.9,425.65 :Hindi/Urdu,^{3} for which we examine three distinct syntactic types of V-V collocations. We argue that these
line=25 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,400.16,538.54,411.07       :morphosyntactically distinct types correlate exactly with three distinct subevental architectures, thus lending
line=26 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.17 bbox=72.0,386.6,305.24,397.51        :support to our view of the syntax-semantics interface.
line=27 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.00 bbox=88.92,373.04,538.92,383.95      :    In what follows, we first lay out the data which furnishes the basis of our discussion. After pointing out
line=28 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,359.48,538.61,370.39       :that light verbs and auxiliaries must be clearly distinguished from one another on phonological and syntactic
line=29 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,345.92,538.9,356.83        :grounds, we  show that the three differing V-V constructions display differences in terms of whether they
line=30 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.28 bbox=72.0,332.36,538.77,343.27       :predicate jointly or separately. We then go on to explain the cluster of properties by proposing that verbs
line=31 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.10 bbox=72.0,318.8,538.89,329.71        :in general can be lexically attached/instantiated as either v, V or as part of a result phrase (R). A verb can
line=32 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.33 bbox=71.99,305.24,538.6,316.15       :be Merged  in the (first phase) syntax as a v, but then must enter into a complex predicate construction
line=33 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.26 bbox=71.99,291.8,538.78,302.71       :with another verbal head or heads to complete the subevental structure. Each verb in the language carries
line=34 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=71.99,278.24,538.91,289.15      :syntactic category features which determine the possible positions of Merge. In the cases where the so-
line=35 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,264.68,538.87,275.59       :called main verb of the construction ends up giving rise to aspectual effects, this is because it has Merged to
line=36 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.15 bbox=71.99,251.12,538.48,262.03      :instantiate the R head (result portion) of the predication. Conversely, when the light verb of the construction
line=37 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=71.99,237.56,538.92,248.47      :appears to contribute some variant on causative semantics, it is because this verb is Merging as v in the
line=38 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.37 bbox=71.99,224.0,538.88,234.91       :first phase syntax. Because of its explicit decompositional morphology, the detailed consideration of the
line=39 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=71.99,210.44,538.89,221.35      :morphosyntax  and semantics of the light verb construction ends up providing overt evidence for a three way
line=40 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.18 bbox=71.99,196.88,538.85,207.79      :categorial decomposition of this type, and contributes invaluable data for investigating the constraints on
line=41 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.33 bbox=71.99,183.32,538.42,194.23      :their modes of combination. Moreover,  the approach presented in this paper allows a novel understanding
line=42 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.17 bbox=71.99,169.76,538.9,180.67       :of the internal mechanics of complex predication, i.e., of the precise manner in which light verb and main
line=43 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=71.99,156.2,273.24,167.11       :verb interact at the syntax/semantics interface.

