line=46 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=72.0,733.28,538.74,744.19                    :Before we turn to the central phenomena, we first outline the basic clause structural properties of Hindi/Urdu
line=47 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,719.84,538.82,730.75        :and its system of tense/aspect marking. Hindi/Urdu is an SOV  (head-final) language with a mixed system
line=48 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,706.28,538.83,717.19        :of periphrastic constructions and tense/aspect inflections. The verb either inflects by itself or co-occurs with
line=49 fonts=F0-10.9,F5-10.9 iscore=0.29 bbox=72.0,692.72,504.63,703.63:inflecting auxiliaries which carry tense and aspect. This is summarized in (1) for the verb mar ‘hit’.

