line=94 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=72.0,556.76,538.81,567.67           :These constructions are formed from what  looks like the stem form of the main verb and an inflecting light
line=95 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.32 bbox=72.0,543.2,538.78,554.11:verb, here illustrated by ‘give’ and ‘take’. They are possibly the most difficult to characterize semanti-
line=96 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.21 bbox=72.0,529.64,538.9,540.55:cally. Traditionally, the addition of the light verb has been said to contribute a range of meanings such as
line=97 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.26 bbox=72.0,516.2,491.55,527.11:completion, inception, benefaction, force, suddenness, etc. (see Hook 1974 for a detailed study).

