line=174 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=88.92,653.36,538.97,664.27                   :    If one considers (8), it can be seen that the auxiliaries have defective paradigms and do not inflect
line=175 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,639.8,538.79,650.71         :according to all possible tenses and aspects in the verbal system; in fact they function to create a number
line=176 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.15 bbox=72.0,626.24,538.9,637.15         :of the tense/aspect meanings in the language. On the other hand, true ‘light’ verbs are not a subclass of the
line=177 fonts=F0-10.9,F5-10.9 iscore=0.05 bbox=72.0,612.68,530.38,623.59:tense/aspect system in this way—they inflect according to all tenses and aspects possible in the language.
line=178 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.16 bbox=88.92,599.12,538.72,610.03       :    From  a syntactic point of view as well, it can be shown that auxiliaries and light verbs have distinct
line=179 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.05 bbox=72.0,585.56,538.69,596.47        :syntactic properties with respect to (at least) case marking, reduplication and topicalization. In the following
line=180 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.07 bbox=72.0,572.0,341.53,582.91         :subsections, we demonstrate each of these diagnostics in turn.

