doc_id=118 page=5 block_id=5-6 bbox=72.0,385.76,539.0,532.15 label=bttb 182 192
line=182 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=72.0,521.24,538.72,532.15                   :Urdu/Hindi  is a split-ergative language: ergative subjects only appear in the perfect tenses (see Davison 1999
line=183 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,507.68,538.79,518.59       :for a very detailed discussion). However, even  in the presence of perfect morphology, the verb’s lexical
line=184 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,494.12,539.0,505.03        :specification is important because only (di)transitive verbs allow ergative case on the subject in the first
line=185 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,480.56,538.87,491.47       :place. In the case of complex predicates, it is possible for there to be a mismatch between the transitivity of
line=186 fonts=F0-10.9,F5-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,467.0,538.58,477.91:the main verb and the light verb. Interestingly, it is the transitivity properties of the light verb that determine
line=187 fonts=F0-10.9,F4-8.0 iscore=0.21 bbox=72.0,453.44,370.79,465.37:the possibility of ergative case marking in this case (see Butt 1995).^{9}
line=188 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=88.92,439.88,538.71,450.79      :    In the example  (9) below, the transitive main verb ‘write’ carries perfect morphology and therefore
line=189 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.13 bbox=72.0,426.32,538.85,437.23       :structurally requires ergative case on the subject. However, in a complex predicate construction ‘write’ can
line=190 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,412.76,538.87,423.67       :be paired up with one of at least two types of V2: the unaccusative light verb ‘fall’ disallows ergative case in
line=191 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,399.2,538.63,410.11        :general, while the light verb ‘take’ requires it. The examples (10) show that the case-marking of the subject
line=192 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.05 bbox=72.0,385.76,484.42,396.67       :is dependent on the requirements of the light verb, rather than that of the main verb on its own.

