line=202 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=88.92,204.44,538.68,215.35           :    If we think of case marking as being dependent  on lexical/argument structural properties of individual
line=203 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,190.88,538.86,201.79:verbs, as is usual, then the relevance of the light verb here is somewhat surprising. At the very least, it shows
line=204 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.29 bbox=72.0,177.32,538.74,188.23:that the light verb does not have the status of an auxiliary, whose contribution to the possibility of ergative
line=205 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,163.76,398.73,174.67:case marking  is entirely restricted to the perfect vs. non-perfect distinction.

