doc_id=118 page=7 block_id=7-2 bbox=72.0,646.28,538.87,711.43 label=tb 249 253
line=249 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=88.92,700.52,538.74,711.43           :    Once  again, the inability of auxiliaries to strand under topicalization seems to correlate with their highly
line=250 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,686.96,514.78,697.87:dependent  and functional nature. This defectiveness is strikingly absent with the ‘light’ verb however.
line=251 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=88.92,673.4,538.64,684.31:    To summarize,  therefore, there is good evidence that light verbs form a distinct subclass, both inflection-
line=252 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,659.84,538.87,670.75:ally and syntactically, from pure auxiliaries in this language. Any analysis which conflates the two types of
line=253 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,646.28,529.13,657.19:construction is simply missing a substantial set of syntactic, semantic and morphological generalizations.

