doc_id=118 page=7 block_id=7-4 bbox=72.0,383.12,539.05,597.31 label=btb 255 270
line=255 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=72.0,586.4,538.85,597.31                     :Light verb constructions are thus clearly differentiable from simple auxiliary cases, and so a standard mono-
line=256 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,572.84,539.05,583.75        :clausal analysis with the light verb in the role of tense/aspect modifier is not immediately tenable. As
line=257 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,559.28,538.91,570.19        :mentioned  before, the other obvious relationship possible between two verbal elements is that of simple
line=258 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,545.72,538.9,556.63         :complementation   to create a biclausal structure. With regard to this second possibility, we will find that
line=259 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,532.16,538.7,543.07         :light verb constructions themselves do not form a unified class. As was already seen, even a superficial
line=260 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,518.6,539.01,529.51         :inspection of the morphology revealed that the types of V-V constructions are distinct. In this section, we
line=261 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,505.04,538.87,515.95        :describe the main syntactic and morphological properties of the three construction types introduced at the
line=262 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,491.48,496.02,502.39        :beginning of the paper and argue that a simple biclausal analysis is possible for only one of them.
line=263 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=88.92,477.92,538.91,488.83       :    Specifically, we must investigate next whether the different complex verbal constructions at issue here
line=264 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.07 bbox=72.0,464.48,538.74,475.39        :project independent clauses with distinct complete functional complexes (CFCs) or whether the verbal heads
line=265 fonts=F0-10.9,F5-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,450.92,538.53,461.83:in question in some way jointly determine a simplex CFC for the sentence. In investigating the monoclausal
line=266 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,437.36,538.7,448.27         :or biclausal status of these constructions in this sense, certain diagnostics from the literature can be applied,
line=267 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,423.8,317.23,434.71         :particularly for Hindi/Urdu (Butt 1995, Mohanan 1994).
line=268 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.00 bbox=88.92,410.24,538.92,421.15       :    To anticipate the results of the following subsections, the tests with respect to anaphora, control and
line=269 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.17 bbox=72.0,396.68,538.88,407.59        :verb agreement  show that the ‘result’ type and the ‘let’ type behave like a single predicational unit, while
line=270 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.22 bbox=72.0,383.12,492.05,394.03        :the ‘tell’ type seems to contain two distinct argument domains and is thus biclausal in this sense.

