line=272 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=72.0,332.36,538.58,343.27                  :Generally in Hindi/Urdu, the descriptive generalization is that the verb agrees with the hierarchically highest
line=273 fonts=F0-10.9,F4-8.0 iscore=0.07 bbox=72.0,318.8,539.17,330.73:nominative argument  (Mohanan   1994).^{10} If there is no nominative argument, masculine singular marking
line=274 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.16 bbox=72.0,305.24,538.68,316.15      :appears on the verb as the default. An inspection of the data below shows that the ‘result’ type construc-
line=275 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.37 bbox=72.0,291.68,538.88,302.59      :tion and the ‘let’ type construction, but not the ‘tell’ type follow the pattern of agreement found in simple
line=276 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.16 bbox=72.0,278.12,538.74,289.03      :clauses. In particular, the internal argument of V1 can trigger agreement on V2 if it is the highest nominative
line=277 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.05 bbox=72.0,264.56,411.11,275.47      :argument  in a sentence of the ‘result’ type (15), and also of the ‘let’ type (16).

