doc_id=118 page=11 block_id=11-1 bbox=72.0,582.08,539.86,804.91 label=t 397 411
line=397 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=529.08,794.0,539.86,804.91            :                                                                                                     11
line=398 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.00 bbox=88.92,758.12,538.92,769.03:    Moreover, while there are certain selectional restrictions at work between the main and the light verb,
line=399 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,744.68,538.52,755.59 :the constructions are also productive, and have an underlying semantics that is regular and compositional:
line=400 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.22 bbox=72.0,731.12,538.89,742.03 :in the case of the ‘let’ type we consistently get the addition of a causer; in the case of the ‘result’ type, the
line=401 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.17 bbox=72.0,717.56,538.72,728.47 :addition of a telos. In our opinion, to ignore these regularities is to ignore an important generalization about
line=402 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.21 bbox=72.0,704.0,538.63,714.91  :the ways in which so-called ‘lexical’ meanings are built up. In what follows, we will argue that the different
line=403 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.26 bbox=72.0,690.44,538.66,701.35 :pieces of the complex predicates here are the instantiations of different heads within an kind of l-syntax
line=404 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,676.88,538.59,687.79 :(cf. Hale and Keyser 1993),  or ‘first phase syntax’ (cf. Ramchand 2002) which  is a syntax representing
line=405 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,663.32,538.38,674.23 :the finely articulated decomposition of the event structure and argument taking properties of predicational
line=406 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.17 bbox=72.0,649.76,538.77,660.67 :items. The paradox of complex predications of this type can be solved if we acknowledge that single lexical
line=407 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.22 bbox=72.0,636.2,538.8,647.11   :items in one language can be lexicalized as separate ‘pieces’ in another language; and that what we think
line=408 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.22 bbox=72.0,622.64,538.62,633.55 :of a lexical item with its argument structure is actually part of a combinatoric system of syntactic structure
line=409 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,609.08,294.23,619.99 :corresponding to an event structure decomposition.
line=410 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.05 bbox=88.92,595.64,539.0,606.55 :    We  turn now to a description of the system and the set of assumptions we will be working with in our
line=411 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.05 bbox=72.0,582.08,206.92,592.99 :analysis of these constructions.

