doc_id=118 page=14 block_id=14-11 bbox=72.0,121.16,539.46,362.35 label=bbbbbb 535 552
line=535 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=88.92,351.44,538.64,362.35                   :    Given the semantics of these various heads, if the heads are not built up in the correct order, the derivation
line=536 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.15 bbox=72.0,337.88,538.92,348.79        :will at best converge as gibberish. Given the existence of this functional sequence, we will assume that
line=537 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.32 bbox=72.0,324.32,538.7,335.23         :the syntactic structures are freely built up by Merge, but that they have to be licensed by the presence
line=538 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.16 bbox=72.0,310.88,538.94,321.79        :of specific lexical items. One of the important features of this system is the way in which lexical items
line=539 fonts=F0-10.9,F5-10.9 iscore=0.32 bbox=72.0,297.32,538.61,308.23:associate to this first phase syntax. Crucially, they do not project the first phase syntax, but simply associate
line=540 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.28 bbox=72.0,283.76,538.87,294.67        :their encyclopaedic lexical content with the semantic skeleton provided by the combinatoric system. There
line=541 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,270.2,538.89,281.11         :are dependencies  in both directions: the syntactic structure needs to be licensed by explicit content to be
line=542 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.29 bbox=72.0,256.64,538.67,267.55        :interpretable at the interface; the lexical item can only associate with a node that matches the category
line=543 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,243.08,538.99,253.99        :features it is listed with. The category labels or ‘tags’ on lexical items are the only information we will find
line=544 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.15 bbox=72.0,229.52,538.63,240.43        :necessary to regulate their use, and moreover the minimal nature of the syntactically relevant information
line=545 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.27 bbox=72.0,215.96,416.37,226.87        :they have will be part of the solution to ‘flexible’ lexical use within a language.
line=546 fonts=F0-10.9,F4-8.0 iscore=0.12 bbox=88.92,202.4,539.46,214.33 :    While the details of the implementation are beyond the scope of this particular paper,^{13} the main intuition
line=547 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.10 bbox=72.0,188.84,538.94,199.75        :is the following: if the lexical item is specified as having the particular category feature (v, V or R or
line=548 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.40 bbox=72.0,175.28,538.91,186.19        :some  combination),  the corresponding syntactic structure is licensed; nominal arguments are merged  in
line=549 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,161.84,538.75,172.75        :the specifier positions of licensed projections and get the interpretation given by the union of the semantic
line=550 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,148.28,465.81,159.19        :compositional rules and the encyclopaedic information carried by the specific lexical item.
line=551 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.00 bbox=88.92,134.72,538.95,145.63       :    As we  have seen, the specifier positions are interpreted systematically by the general semantic com-
line=552 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,121.16,538.78,132.07        :ponent  as: Initiator, Undergoer and Resultee respectively. There are thus no thematic  roles, only three

doc_id=118 page=15 block_id=15-1 bbox=72.0,378.8,539.86,804.91 label=t 553 582
line=553 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=529.08,794.0,539.86,804.91           :                                                                                                    15
line=554 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.00 bbox=72.0,758.12,538.86,769.03:universal semantic rules triggered by syntactic structure. One major departure this proposal will make from
line=555 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,744.68,538.87,755.59:other systems is that these specifier positions are not claimed to be mutually exclusive. In other words, it is
line=556 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.37 bbox=72.0,731.12,538.78,742.03:possible for a single argument to be in more than one of these positions simultaneously (or have them linked
line=557 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.21 bbox=72.0,717.56,538.79,728.47:together in an A-chain). This means that we are assuming that there is no -Criterion, and that the semantic
line=558 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.16 bbox=72.0,704.0,538.86,714.91 :interpretations of the positions so linked get unified. In principle, there is no incompatibility between the
line=559 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,690.44,528.91,701.35:semantics of Initiator, Undergoer, Resultee, and so no violations will occur purely because of unification.
line=560 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.17 bbox=88.92,676.88,538.8,687.79:    With respect to the particulars of the first phase syntax proposed, the elements of the ontology are those
line=561 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.22 bbox=72.0,663.32,538.65,674.23:which have proved  over the years to be minimally necessary to express the linguistically relevant argument
line=562 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.19 bbox=72.0,649.76,539.05,660.67:structure and aspectual distinctions found in natural language. Thus, causation has been shown to be a
line=563 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,636.2,538.81,647.11 :relevant parameter in verbal differences and shows up very often as overt morphology within the verbal
line=564 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.19 bbox=72.0,622.64,538.71,633.55:inventory of human  languages (cf. Baker 1988, Hale and Keyser 1993, Ritter and Rosen 1998, Rappoport
line=565 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,609.08,538.73,619.99:Hovav  and Levin  2000).  Telos or resultativity is also a component that has been shown to be isolable
line=566 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.22 bbox=72.0,595.64,538.97,606.55:as a parameter in verbal meanings, and  which  has associated morphology  and case marking  reflexes in
line=567 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.19 bbox=72.0,582.08,538.84,592.99:various languages (see for example Tenny  1994, Kiparsky 1998,  van Hout 1996, Ritter and Rosen  1998,
line=568 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,568.52,538.61,579.43:Borer 1998). The decomposition  proposed here takes those generalizations seriously, and explicitly encodes
line=569 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.27 bbox=72.0,554.96,538.89,565.87:subevents to represent each isolable component, each correlated with a functional projection in the ‘first
line=570 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,541.4,538.67,552.31 :phase syntax’. The projection VP, corresponding to the process component is the only one that we consider
line=571 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.22 bbox=72.0,527.84,538.86,538.75:to be obligatory for all (non-stative) verbs since it represents the concept of change, a crucial component of
line=572 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,514.28,538.84,525.19:any non-stative (in its most degenerate version can reduce to a single transition, but this for us still counts as
line=573 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.15 bbox=72.0,500.72,538.9,511.63 :change/process). The concept of change in this extremely general sense is a presupposed condition for the
line=574 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,487.16,256.49,498.07:concepts both of initiation and result state.
line=575 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.07 bbox=88.92,473.6,538.95,484.51:    We  exploit these ideas of event structure decomposition and use the Hindi/Urdu V-V constructions as
line=576 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,460.04,538.68,470.95:a test-bed for the formulation proposed here of the syntactic conditions on the ways that event building
line=577 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.41 bbox=72.0,446.6,538.79,457.51 :can occur in the grammar. We  believe that causation and telic pair formation are the fundamental semantic
line=578 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,433.04,538.75,443.95:combinatoric operations available in the grammars of natural language and that they are more primitive than
line=579 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,419.48,538.77,430.39:other sorts of semantic relationships that can obtain between events. We believe further that the complex
line=580 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,405.92,538.64,416.83:predicate data from Hindi/Urdu provides direct justification for the nature of the decomposition proposed
line=581 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,392.36,538.86,403.27:here and its relationship to syntactic representation. The explicitly constructionalist view taken is also
line=582 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.21 bbox=72.0,378.8,533.61,389.71 :important because only such a view is able to make sense of the event structure flexibility of lexical items.

