line=585 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=72.0,297.56,538.72,308.47            :Recall that the ‘let’ type of construction showed syntactic evidence for monoclausality while still maintain-
line=586 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,284.0,539.05,294.91 :ing the two verbs as separable syntactic, semantic and prosodic elements. We therefore cannot assume  a
line=587 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,270.44,538.79,281.35:direct theta-marking relationship between the event introduced by V1 and that introduced by V2 for these
line=588 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.19 bbox=72.0,256.88,538.71,267.79:constructions, since that would give rise to two distinct predicational domains. Further, the light verb cannot
