doc_id=118 page=18 block_id=18-6 bbox=72.0,191.6,539.5,514.15 label=bbtb 684 707
line=684 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=72.0,503.24,538.84,514.15                 :In this section we return to the question of the representation of the ‘result’ type of complex predicate. Recall
line=685 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.16 bbox=72.0,489.68,538.39,500.59     :that these V-V sequences also exhibited syntactic and semantic integrity with respect to our predicational
line=686 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.19 bbox=72.0,476.12,538.93,487.03     :diagnostics, which once  again commits  us to a monoclausal  structure, even though these light verbs are
line=687 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,462.56,538.47,473.47     :clearly not auxiliaries. In addition, the ‘result’ type constructions seem to have accomplishment interpreta-
line=688 fonts=F0-10.9,F4-8.0 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,449.0,539.5,460.93:tions, regardless of the particular choice of light verb involved.^{17} Semantically, then, this is an example of
line=689 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,435.44,240.35,446.35     :productive accomplishment  formation.
line=690 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.00 bbox=88.92,421.88,538.72,432.79    :    Once  again, we believe the apparent paradox of the behaviour of these constructions can be resolved
line=691 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,408.44,538.8,419.35      :if we see the meaning  composition as being related to the event structure decomposition that takes place
line=692 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.16 bbox=72.0,394.88,538.84,405.79     :in a first phase syntax. We do not believe it is an accident that the creation of accomplishment seman-
line=693 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,381.32,538.92,392.23     :tics is associated with the paradoxical properties we have found. The first phase syntax motivated in the
line=694 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,367.76,538.64,378.67     :previous section, drawing on many  empirical observations in the literature concerning argument structure
line=695 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,354.2,538.83,365.11      :alternations etc., isolates telic augmentation as one of the crucial modulations between related lexical items
line=696 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.13 bbox=72.0,340.64,538.87,351.55     :(either through productive morphological processes, or even ‘null’ derivation). Here we find that very same
line=697 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.15 bbox=72.0,327.08,538.78,337.99     :modulation, but this time mediated by the use of a light verb in a V-V construction. The collocation in ques-
line=698 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,313.52,538.59,324.43     :tion has properties that indicate integrity with respect to determining argument structure and event structure
line=699 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,299.96,344.17,310.87     :properties, just as one would expect from a single lexical item.
line=700 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=88.92,286.4,538.66,297.31     :    We  take this as further confirmation of the linguistic reality of the decomposition of so-called ‘lexical’
line=701 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,272.84,538.83,283.75     :meanings  that we are calling first phase syntax. The test of the specific proposal lies in the very clear
line=702 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,259.4,538.92,270.31      :predictions it makes about the syntactic form of an accomplishment predicate if it were to be composed of
line=703 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.22 bbox=72.0,245.84,538.56,256.75     :distinct heads. Under the proposal being entertained here, the RP is the lowest down  in the hierarchical
line=704 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,232.28,538.67,243.19     :ordering within the first phase syntax. We would therefore expect, in a descriptively head final language,
line=705 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.17 bbox=72.0,218.72,538.99,229.63     :that the individual piece of the structure that represents the final state attained would be linearly the first
line=706 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.26 bbox=72.0,205.16,539.01,216.07     :element of the construction. This indeed is what we find. In the ‘result’ type construction, the main verb V1
line=707 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.16 bbox=72.0,191.6,316.74,202.51      :describes the final state achieved as a result of the event.

