line=725 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=88.92,548.24,538.96,559.15                           :    Note that analysing the V1 here as an R head  is superficially at odds with the descriptive statement in
line=726 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.21 bbox=72.0,534.68,538.83,545.59                :the literature that the light verb in these constructions is what is responsible for adding the telicity (see Hook
line=727 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.21 bbox=72.0,521.12,539.06,532.03                :1991, Singh  1994).  However,  the descriptive statement can easily be reconciled with the facts once we
line=728 fonts=F0-10.9,F5-10.9 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,507.68,538.87,518.59        :realize that it is the light verb that selects for an RP in this structure and thus in a way is responsible for the
line=729 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,494.12,538.91,505.03                :accomplishment   reading, although the actual description of the final state achieved is V1. In fact, we can
line=730 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.19 bbox=72.0,480.56,538.74,491.47                :see that the crucial contribution of the V2 here is as the process descriptor, since it is this head that selects
line=731 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.33 bbox=72.0,467.0,538.88,477.91                 :the RP. The existence of a little v, or causing component is not essential to this particular construction. In
line=732 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,453.44,538.78,464.35                :(46a) the complex  predicate indicates a caused process that achieves a particular final state, but in (46b)
line=733 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.21 bbox=72.0,439.88,538.87,450.79                :there is no causer, just a process that is undergone and gives rise to a final state. In (46b), the light verb is an
line=734 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.17 bbox=72.0,426.32,454.82,437.23                :‘unaccusative’ verb, which we take to mean that it does not identify a little v head at all.
line=735 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=88.92,412.76,538.78,423.67               :    If the V1 describes the final state achieved, then V2 must be responsible for instantiating the process head
line=736 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.10 bbox=72.0,399.2,538.61,410.11                 :at least, and possibly the little v causational head as well in the case of light verbs derived from transitives.
line=737 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.29 bbox=72.0,385.64,538.43,396.55                :It is not unusual in itself for a single lexical item to identify both V and v, since under a decompositional
line=738 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.10 bbox=72.0,372.08,538.8,382.99                 :account this is what main verbs do all the time. However, since the result of the process is V1, this forces
line=739 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,358.64,538.86,369.55                :the cause-process component  of the meaning to be fairly abstract—in fact, light verbs like ‘take’ , ‘give’ and
line=740 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,345.08,335.18,355.99                :‘go’ found in this construction have fairly general meanings.
line=741 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=88.92,331.52,499.78,342.43               :    Thus, we propose  that the schematic representation for a forms like (47a) would be as follows.
line=742 fonts=F0-10.9,F0-23.4,F12-23.3 iscore=0.19 bbox=75.6,305.96,199.0,329.33: (49) e: e = (e8 9 ) : e; , e< =

