doc_id=118 page=21 block_id=21-3 bbox=72.0,382.4,538.96,610.03 label=btb 788 804
line=788 fonts=F0-10.9 bbox=72.0,599.12,538.88,610.03             :Comparing   the structures proposed for the ‘let’ type and the ‘result’ type, both constructions deserve the
line=789 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,585.56,538.9,596.47  :label of ‘complex predicate’, because in each type the two verbal heads are instantiations of heads within
line=790 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,572.0,538.78,582.91  :the first phase syntax. This gives them a privileged status in the constructing of the core event at the heart
line=791 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.10 bbox=72.0,558.44,538.92,569.35 :of the proposition and in the determination of argument structure and case marking. They demonstrate an
line=792 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.19 bbox=72.0,545.0,537.2,555.91   :internal integrity which is often found within single lexical items in more well known European languages.
line=793 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.00 bbox=88.92,531.44,538.9,542.35 :    There is a difference between the two types as well: in the ‘let’ construction, the light verb is simply the
line=794 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.15 bbox=72.0,517.88,538.75,528.79 :little v head and it determines its own ‘causer’ argument in Spec, vP; in the ‘result’ construction, the light
line=795 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,504.32,538.94,515.23 :verb instantiates the process head and the main verb the result head, but the argument in Spec, RP is the
line=796 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,490.76,538.88,501.67 :same  as the argument in Spec, VP. Essentially, while in the ‘let’ construction is it possible to separate the
line=797 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.16 bbox=72.0,477.2,538.64,488.11  :contribution of the two parts of the complex predicate cleanly, each with its own arguments, in the ‘result’
line=798 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.22 bbox=72.0,463.64,538.81,474.55 :construction, separating the light verb from the main verb would mean  separating a verb from its direct
line=799 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,450.08,115.34,460.99 :argument.
line=800 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.00 bbox=88.92,436.52,538.96,447.43:    There is in fact evidence for a difference in movement possibilities when the two constructions are
line=801 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,422.96,538.63,433.87 :compared  closely with respect to scrambling. As we indicated before, both constructions can feed a topical-
line=802 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.31 bbox=72.0,409.4,538.62,420.31  :ization structure where the light verb is fronted. However, in simple scrambling constructions, scrambling
line=803 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.05 bbox=72.0,395.96,538.89,406.87 :of main verb with its object away from the light verb is possible in the ‘let’ complex predicate (53) , but not
line=804 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.05 bbox=72.0,382.4,236.75,393.31  :in the ‘result’ complex predicate (54).

