line=899 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.00 bbox=88.92,758.12,538.93,769.03:    To summarize,  we think that a constructional syntactic analysis of complex predicates is the most suc-
line=900 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,744.68,538.8,755.59  :cessful at dealing with the syntactic semantic and word order properties of these two types of V-V collo-
line=901 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,731.12,538.94,742.03 :cation. The  special status of first phase syntax as the decomposition of the components within the core
line=902 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,717.56,538.65,728.47 :event structure of the clause accounts for its special properties in terms of the determination of argument
line=903 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.35 bbox=72.0,704.0,538.62,714.91  :structure, case marking and aktionsart, and also for the parallels to single lexical items across languages.
line=904 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.19 bbox=72.0,690.44,538.64,701.35 :The syntactic approach in addition, makes quite specific predictions about the interpretation, morphology
line=905 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,676.88,538.92,687.79 :and distributional properties of the individual lexical components that could be used to build up vPs in
line=906 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,663.32,538.79,674.23 :languages that have the appropriate lexical ingredients. Hindi/Urdu is such a language, and its complex
line=907 fonts=F0-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,649.76,391.96,660.67 :predicates provide a wealth of data confirming many of those predictions.

